CharacterCreated(uint24).details: Emitted when the character with "id" is created.

Fighted(uint24,uint24,uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when the character with "myTokenId" removes "substrateLifeToRival" points of hp to "rivalTokenId" and the character with "rivalTokenId" removes "substrateLifeToMe" points of hp to "myTokenId".

LevelUp(uint24,uint16).details: Emitted when the character with "tokenId" has gained enough experience points to increase one level.

LimitUpdated(uint24).details: Emitted when the owner changes the mintable NFT limit with the amount "limitMint".

MintFeeUpdated(uint256).details: Emitted when the owner changes the ether fee for minting, with the amount "mintFee".

PotionUsed(uint24).details: Emitted when the msg.sender burn a potion.

Rested(uint24).details: Emitted when the character with "id" is rested, he recovers health points and stamina.

StuffBought(uint16).details: Emitted when the msg.sender buy a stuff ".

StuffEquiped(uint24,uint16).details: Emitted when the msg.sender burn a potion.

StuffFeeUpdated(uint256).details: Emitted when the owner changes the ether fee for buying stuff, with the amount "stuffFee".

attributesLevelUp(uint24,uint24,uint24,u.details: The function allows the allocation of "attributePoints" to the different characteristics.

balanceOf(address,uint256).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOf}. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

buyStuff(uint16).details: The function allows you to buy a stuff NFT

params.stuffId: Id of the stuff. Emits a "StuffBought" event.

constructor.details: Constructor of the contract ERC1155, mint stuff and add it to the mapping

params._genderCharacter: Gender of character between MASCULINE, FEMININE, OTHER. Emits a "CharacterCreated" event.
params._typeCharacter: Type of character between BRUTE, SPIRITUAL, ELEMENTARY.

equipStuff(uint24,uint16).details: The function allows you to equip stuff to your NFT

params.stuffId: Id of the stuff to equip. Emits a "StuffEquiped" event.

fight(uint24,uint24).details: The function allows you to use your NFT to fight with another NFT belonging to another user.

getMyCharacters().details: The function returns an array with the characteristics of all my NFTs.

getOthersCharacters().details: The function returns an array with the characteristics of all the NFTs that don't belong to me.

getTokenDetails(uint24).details: The function returns the characteristics of the NFT.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

rest(uint24).details: The function allows the NFT to recover 100 health points and 100 stamina points.

params._tokenId: Id of the token. Emits a "Rested" event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateLimitMint(uint24).details: The function changes the mintable NFT limit.

params._limitMint: New limit of mintable NFT. Emits a "LimitUpdated" event.

updateMintFee(uint256).details: The function changes the ether fee for minting.

params._mintFee: New amount of fee. Emits a "MintFeeUpdated" event.

updateStuffFee(uint256).details: The function changes the ether fee for buying stuff.

params._stuffFee: New amount of stuff fee. Emits a "StuffFeeUpdated" event.

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.

usePotion(uint24).details: The function burn a POTION and restore the hp and stamina of your NFT

params.tokenId: Id of the token. Emits a "PotionUsed" event.

withdraw().details: Owner withdraws the entire amount of ETH.

withdrawLINK(uint256).details: Owner withdraws an amount of LINK.
